WEBVTT

00:02.769 --> 00:03.802
[ Remote clicks ]

00:03.837 --> 00:05.371
[ Upbeat music plays ]

00:07.908 --> 00:10.776
♪ I don't care what you say! ♪

00:12.112 --> 00:14.079
♪ I'm gonna do what I want
all day! ♪

00:14.114 --> 00:16.715
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:16.750 --> 00:18.650
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:18.685 --> 00:23.088
♪ I'm the king of the world!
I'm the king of the world! ♪

00:25.592 --> 00:28.227
♪♪

00:29.796 --> 00:31.696
-Choo-choo!
-[ Laughing ]

00:31.731 --> 00:34.499
Chad train pulling into
the station!

00:34.534 --> 00:37.002
Well, bud, are we at
the right school this time?

00:37.037 --> 00:39.271
Yes, I think this is it.

00:39.306 --> 00:41.239
Okay, then.
Have fun today, bud!

00:41.274 --> 00:43.575
[ Laughs ]
Thanks Train Chad!

00:43.610 --> 00:46.511
You were probably wondering
when I would assign

00:46.546 --> 00:47.446
your next essay.

00:47.481 --> 00:48.880
[ Class groans ]
[ Gasps ]

00:48.915 --> 00:50.916
I know, I know,
but this'll be fun!

00:50.951 --> 00:53.585
I want you to write about
someone you admire.

00:53.620 --> 00:55.954
Okay, it could be your mom,
your day, anyone!

00:55.989 --> 00:57.589
Ms. Baker,
could it be my aunt?

00:57.624 --> 00:58.757
Yeah, sure, Chelsea.

00:58.792 --> 01:00.225
Ooh, ooh,
could it be my uncle?

01:00.260 --> 01:02.227
Yeah, Jeff. It -- yeah,
it could be your uncle.

01:02.262 --> 01:02.928
Yesss!

01:02.963 --> 01:05.597
Someone you admire...

01:05.632 --> 01:07.099
Hmm...

01:07.134 --> 01:08.767
[ Crunching ]
Mmm...mmm!

01:08.802 --> 01:10.202
Hey, Chad, um,

01:10.237 --> 01:12.104
Mom said we're not supposed
to eat on the couch

01:12.139 --> 01:14.106
'cause we get crumbs
on the couch.

01:14.141 --> 01:17.275
It's okay! Mnh.
Just this once.

01:17.310 --> 01:19.211
Heh, just this once.

01:19.246 --> 01:20.078
[ Chomp! ]

01:20.113 --> 01:20.879
[ Munching ]

01:20.914 --> 01:22.447
Oh, yeah, um, Chad,

01:22.482 --> 01:24.049
can you sign this?

01:24.084 --> 01:26.651
You didn't climb the rope
in gym class?

01:26.686 --> 01:28.653
Wendle! Up that rope, sir!
Up, up, up!

01:28.688 --> 01:30.622
Come on, Clarence!
You can do this!

01:30.657 --> 01:32.457
I can't do that.
That's high. Sorry.

01:32.492 --> 01:34.793
What happened, bud?
Why didn't you do it?

01:34.828 --> 01:38.296
I was gonna, but...
I'm just not tough.

01:38.331 --> 01:41.766
Like Vu, he climbed
that rope so good.

01:41.801 --> 01:43.468
[ All cheering ]

01:43.503 --> 01:44.836
[ Bell rings ]

01:44.871 --> 01:48.006
Yeah, you still got to,
like, try, you know?

01:48.041 --> 01:49.441
I mean,
you can do anything!

01:49.476 --> 01:50.742
You never do anything,

01:50.777 --> 01:52.677
and you're the coolest guy
that I know!

01:52.712 --> 01:55.113
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:55.148 --> 01:58.416
Oh, man, I should ask you
my essay questions.

01:58.451 --> 01:59.784
Okay...

01:59.819 --> 02:03.655
Okay, Chad, first question --
who are you?

02:03.690 --> 02:05.524
Umm...Chad.

02:05.559 --> 02:07.692
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.
And, uh...

02:07.727 --> 02:09.828
what do you do
for a living?

02:09.863 --> 02:15.600
Uh...various careers
in, um...stuff.

02:15.635 --> 02:16.501
And, um...

02:16.536 --> 02:17.502
[ Twang! ]

02:17.537 --> 02:18.803
...some music training.

02:18.838 --> 02:20.705
Nice! Okay, next.

02:20.740 --> 02:23.475
What are some goals
you've achieved?

02:23.510 --> 02:26.344
[ Nervously ] Well, I found
$5 in the gutter last week.

02:26.379 --> 02:29.514
Heh, I hope I can
find $5 some day.

02:29.549 --> 02:30.849
Just don't give up!

02:30.884 --> 02:33.885
What's a goal you hope
to achieve in the future?

02:33.920 --> 02:36.688
Uh...uh...

02:36.723 --> 02:39.824
I'm gonna...
I'm gonna...um...

02:39.859 --> 02:41.293
I'm gonna...

02:41.328 --> 02:42.494
♪♪

02:42.529 --> 02:43.361
[ Crowd cheers ]

02:43.396 --> 02:44.629
[ Twinkle! ]

02:44.664 --> 02:45.830
I'm...

02:45.865 --> 02:48.400
gonna run
the Aberdale Marathon!

02:48.435 --> 02:49.968
Yeah! Whoo!

02:50.003 --> 02:53.738
I'm going to run, uh...
13.1 miles!

02:53.773 --> 02:55.040
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

02:55.075 --> 02:56.474
[ Tauntingly ]
- But here's the thing, bud --

02:56.509 --> 02:59.177
I don't know if I can
do this on my own.

02:59.212 --> 03:01.813
What?! You can't do it
on your own?

03:01.848 --> 03:03.582
Uh, I need a coach.

03:03.617 --> 03:04.916
<i>You</i> need a coach?

03:04.951 --> 03:06.418
Someone to help me.

03:06.453 --> 03:07.586
Someone to help you?

03:07.621 --> 03:08.587
Clarence!
- Chad.

03:08.622 --> 03:09.654
-Clarence!
-Chad!

03:09.689 --> 03:11.389
Will you be my coach?

03:11.424 --> 03:13.191
Yes! I'll do it!

03:13.226 --> 03:14.926
I'm gonna run
a marathon!

03:14.961 --> 03:15.827
I'm gonna coach!

03:15.862 --> 03:16.761
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

03:16.796 --> 03:17.896
I'm gonna coach!

03:17.931 --> 03:19.497
[ Dramatic music plays ]

03:19.532 --> 03:20.365
[ Grunting ]

03:20.400 --> 03:21.566
Come on, Chad,
you got this!

03:21.601 --> 03:22.734
Come on, you got it!

03:22.769 --> 03:23.668
You're doing it!

03:23.703 --> 03:24.703
You're really doing it!

03:24.738 --> 03:25.770
Come on! [ Laughs ]

03:25.805 --> 03:27.539
Whoa! This is amazing!

03:27.574 --> 03:29.941
I've never felt so good!
I can take on any--

03:29.976 --> 03:31.042
[ Record scratches ]

03:31.077 --> 03:31.910
-[ Panting ]
-Chad? Chad.

03:31.945 --> 03:32.911
Hey, Chad?

03:32.946 --> 03:35.080
Hello? Chad. Chad?

03:35.115 --> 03:37.749
Chad? Hey, Chad.

03:37.784 --> 03:41.386
[ Gasping ] I'm gonna need...
a lot of work, Coach...

03:41.421 --> 03:44.422
You sure you're up
for it?

03:44.457 --> 03:46.925
[ Grunts ]

03:46.960 --> 03:49.294
[ Grunts, chuckles ]

03:50.597 --> 03:51.930
Rah!

03:51.965 --> 03:55.233
♪ I've never felt
this powerful before ♪

03:55.268 --> 03:57.802
♪♪

03:57.837 --> 03:59.271
♪ The plan is set ♪

03:59.306 --> 04:02.974
♪ I'm rising with the dawn ♪
[ Rooster crows ]

04:03.009 --> 04:05.443
♪ Dawn ♪

04:05.478 --> 04:06.878
♪ I'm waking up ♪

04:06.913 --> 04:08.280
[ Honk! ]
Aah!

04:08.315 --> 04:11.449
[ Whistle blows ]
♪ My feet are burning ♪

04:11.484 --> 04:14.753
♪ My heart is yearning ♪
[ Honk! Honk! Honk! ]

04:14.788 --> 04:17.255
♪ My feet are burning ♪

04:17.290 --> 04:17.922
Aah!

04:17.957 --> 04:20.492
♪ To win ♪

04:25.432 --> 04:31.636
Aah! - ♪ Body, mind, and
spirit in the mix ♪

04:31.671 --> 04:33.672
♪ When it's tough,
I'll smile ♪

04:33.707 --> 04:35.006
[ Burps ]

04:35.041 --> 04:39.778
♪ And grit my teeth
to tiny bits ♪

04:39.813 --> 04:41.846
♪ I'm shaping up ♪

04:41.881 --> 04:45.317
♪ My feet are burning ♪
[ Snap! Snap! Snap! ]

04:45.352 --> 04:49.020
♪ My heart is yearning ♪

04:49.055 --> 04:51.656
♪ For eggs ♪

04:51.691 --> 04:53.291
What service!
[ Chuckles ]

04:53.326 --> 04:54.826
Never thought my boys
would become a couple

04:54.861 --> 04:56.328
of early birds over here.

04:56.363 --> 04:57.829
[ Squish! Squish! ]
Hello, hello.

04:57.864 --> 05:00.031
[ Chuckles ]
Maaaare...

05:00.066 --> 05:02.867
[ Muffled ] Mom, did you
know Chad can do anything?

05:02.902 --> 05:04.536
Yeah, yeah, sure.
[ Snoring ]

05:04.571 --> 05:06.705
[ Chuckles ] Mom,
that's Chad's food.

05:06.740 --> 05:07.673
[ Munching ]

05:08.875 --> 05:10.508
So, I checked these out.

05:10.543 --> 05:14.512
lots of good info here
about VO-2 Max and lactic acid.

05:14.547 --> 05:16.348
And I brought some gels!

05:16.383 --> 05:17.982
You eat them while you run.

05:18.017 --> 05:19.484
[ Squish! ]
It's slime...

05:19.519 --> 05:22.554
I guess they help replenish
glis-- gly-- glycugen.

05:22.589 --> 05:25.323
I brought all my dogs!
[ Dog snoring ]

05:25.358 --> 05:28.159
I thought we'd run with Chad
like a real wolf pack!

05:28.194 --> 05:29.694
[ Sumo howling ]

05:29.729 --> 05:30.729
[ Clarence howling ]

05:30.764 --> 05:31.896
Bark, bark! [ Laughs ]

05:31.931 --> 05:33.331
Oh, I almost forgot!

05:33.366 --> 05:35.567
We gotta put these bandages
on our nipples.

05:36.903 --> 05:38.336
It says so right here!

05:38.371 --> 05:39.571
"During prolonged jogs,

05:39.606 --> 05:41.473
shirt fabric rubs against
the nipple

05:41.508 --> 05:45.043
causing irritation
and in some extreme cases..."

05:45.078 --> 05:47.045
the dreaded bloody nipple.

05:47.080 --> 05:48.646
[ Both shudder ]

05:48.681 --> 05:49.881
[ Both grunting ]

05:49.916 --> 05:51.249
[ Grunts ]

05:51.284 --> 05:52.650
Can't be too careful.

05:52.685 --> 05:54.552
-Mm-hmm. Uh, yeah.
-Well, uh, there we go.

05:54.587 --> 05:56.755
Well, thanks for helping me
coach Chad, you guys. Huh?

05:56.790 --> 05:58.823
You don't really think
he can do it, do you?

05:58.858 --> 06:01.559
I mean, people train
for years for this stuff.

06:01.594 --> 06:04.095
You can't suddenly decide
you're a runner.

06:04.130 --> 06:05.864
You're either somebody
who does this stuff

06:05.899 --> 06:06.998
or somebody who doesn't.

06:07.033 --> 06:08.533
[ Groans ]

06:08.568 --> 06:11.169
Jeff, are you even listening
to what you're saying?!

06:11.204 --> 06:13.238
Even babies gotta learn
how to walk, right?

06:13.273 --> 06:15.440
I mean,
you're not born as a baby

06:15.475 --> 06:17.876
that's running
on little baby legs.

06:17.911 --> 06:22.013
Chad can do anything he wants
or he can do nothing he wants.

06:22.048 --> 06:23.515
I don't care! He's Chad,

06:23.550 --> 06:26.050
and I'm going to be there
no matter what he does!

06:26.085 --> 06:28.920
Yeah! Hey, who's up
for a little jog?

06:28.955 --> 06:30.088
What the...?

06:30.123 --> 06:31.423
-Go, Chad, go!
-You got this!

06:31.458 --> 06:32.590
-Whoo-hoo!
-Go! Go! Go!

06:32.625 --> 06:34.759
-You got this!
-Yeah! You got it!

06:34.794 --> 06:37.462
[ Dogs barking, all cheering ]

06:37.497 --> 06:39.931
Hey, guys! Wait up!
[ Laughs ]

06:39.966 --> 06:42.467
And do you, Jared,

06:42.502 --> 06:45.470
take this woman to be
your lawfully wedded...

06:45.505 --> 06:46.438
[ Dogs barking ]

06:46.473 --> 06:49.140
Oh, my, it's some
kind of parade!

06:49.175 --> 06:51.276
Come on, Chad!
You can do this!

06:51.311 --> 06:52.877
Oh, hello th--
[ Muffled grunting ]

06:52.912 --> 06:55.146
Oh, no. Oh, good pooch!

06:55.181 --> 06:56.614
[ Grunting ]

06:56.649 --> 07:00.151
Welcome to
- the Aberdale Half Marathon!

07:00.186 --> 07:02.620
Brought to you by Cheezos.

07:02.655 --> 07:03.455
[ Crowd murmuring ]

07:03.490 --> 07:05.557
Well, I guess this is it.

07:05.592 --> 07:08.092
Hey, your coach and I
are very proud of you.

07:08.127 --> 07:11.629
Yeah! And we made you
something special.

07:11.664 --> 07:12.497
Oh, wow!

07:12.532 --> 07:13.998
[ Chuckles ]
Here's you running

07:14.033 --> 07:16.601
and this is where I say
"Go, Chad, go!"

07:16.636 --> 07:18.803
And on the back,
this is what's, uh,

07:18.838 --> 07:20.338
Sumo's dogs that he drew.

07:20.373 --> 07:22.974
Oh, and Jeff wrote this.

07:23.009 --> 07:24.175
Do you like it?

07:24.210 --> 07:25.844
Oh, I love it.

07:25.879 --> 07:29.647
[ Grunts ]

07:29.682 --> 07:32.984
One minute left,
you running fools!

07:33.019 --> 07:34.085
-Oh, I gotta go!
-Yeah, Cheezos!

07:34.120 --> 07:35.420
-Okay. Mwah!
-[ Smooches ]

07:35.455 --> 07:37.155
-Boop! Oh!
-Eat 'em while you run,

07:37.190 --> 07:38.256
that's what I say.

07:38.291 --> 07:39.290
But I like 'em, too.

07:39.325 --> 07:40.658
[ Runners murmuring ]

07:40.693 --> 07:43.194
[ Laughs ]
Yeah, I don't think so.

07:43.229 --> 07:45.830
Well, tell her she's wrong,
then. That's what I do.

07:45.865 --> 07:47.165
[ Twinkle! ]

07:47.200 --> 07:48.333
Okay, race is starting.

07:48.368 --> 07:49.601
[ Oogaaaaah! ]

07:49.636 --> 07:51.002
No, it's just
- a half marathon, no big deal.

07:51.037 --> 07:52.370
Walk in the park,
literally.

07:52.405 --> 07:54.205
'Kay, see you at lunch.

07:54.240 --> 07:56.441
Wow! Well, what,
did your kid make that?

07:56.476 --> 07:57.475
Yeah!

07:57.510 --> 07:59.711
That cotton is gonna
chafe you like crazy.

07:59.746 --> 08:01.546
Heh, newbie, huh?
First race?

08:01.581 --> 08:02.614
[ Nervously ]
Yeah, man.

08:02.649 --> 08:04.048
[ Chuckles ]
Ready to rock!

08:04.083 --> 08:05.350
'Kay, well, that's
a brave attitude.

08:05.385 --> 08:07.185
I think it's very brave
what you're doing.

08:07.220 --> 08:09.120
I mean, we're just
running, right?

08:09.155 --> 08:13.491
ALL: 10, 9, 8, 7, 6...

08:13.526 --> 08:16.861
I believe in you, Chad.
You can do anything.

08:16.896 --> 08:19.731
5, 4, 3, 2, 1...

08:19.766 --> 08:23.034
[ Air horn blows ]

08:23.069 --> 08:24.836
[ Crowd gasps ]

08:24.871 --> 08:28.239
[ Panting ] I'm doing it!
I'm running a marathon!

08:28.274 --> 08:29.407
[ Crowd cheering ]

08:29.442 --> 08:31.476
Come on, Chad!
You got it!

08:31.511 --> 08:33.311
Keep going, you got this!

08:33.346 --> 08:36.314
Chad: Oh, yeah!

08:36.349 --> 08:38.917
Oh, yeah,
I feel so free!

08:38.952 --> 08:40.485
♪♪

08:40.520 --> 08:43.221
[ Echoing, distorted voice ]
I believe in you, Chad.

08:43.256 --> 08:45.890
Oh, here we go!

08:45.925 --> 08:48.359
Yeah! Aah!

08:48.394 --> 08:51.897
[ Laughing ]

08:56.202 --> 09:00.572
[ Panting ]

09:00.607 --> 09:02.407
Mile 2? Aah!

09:02.442 --> 09:04.075
I'm only at mile 2?!

09:04.110 --> 09:05.743
Aah! Aah!

09:05.778 --> 09:07.111
[ Groans ]

09:07.146 --> 09:10.415
Huh?

09:10.450 --> 09:13.851
Oh, no.
Oh, no, oh, ohh.

09:13.886 --> 09:16.754
Chad, get in the car, hon.
It -- it was a great try.

09:16.789 --> 09:19.591
No, Chad, keep running!
Don't get in the car!

09:19.626 --> 09:21.225
This is your coach,
Clarence, speaking.

09:21.260 --> 09:22.093
Um... [ Gasping ]

09:22.128 --> 09:23.027
No!

09:23.062 --> 09:24.028
[ Panting ]

09:24.063 --> 09:25.063
Aah!

09:25.098 --> 09:28.166
[ Grunting ]

09:31.638 --> 09:33.838
[ Screaming ]

09:34.774 --> 09:37.442
Okay. [Chuckles]
- maybe you can give up now.

09:37.477 --> 09:41.279
Hey, at least, uh,
you tried, Chad.

09:41.314 --> 09:42.747
[ Breathes deeply ]

09:42.782 --> 09:46.551
I guess...people can't
do<i> anything</i> they wanna do.

09:46.586 --> 09:50.488
No, buddy...
you<i> can</i> do anything.

09:50.523 --> 09:53.291
But, like...it's hard.

09:53.326 --> 09:55.760
Sometimes
it's really hard.

09:55.795 --> 09:58.296
Look, you did all this
to impress Clarence,

09:58.331 --> 10:00.131
and he's really impressed!

10:00.166 --> 10:01.466
You don't gotta push
yourself.

10:01.501 --> 10:04.769
Yeah, it's okay, Chad.
[ Chuckles ] Let's go home.

10:04.804 --> 10:06.738
Just this once.

10:06.773 --> 10:10.074
Yeah, I...wasn't really
doing this for Clarence.

10:10.109 --> 10:13.111
I was doing it for me.

10:13.146 --> 10:14.612
[ Creaks ]

10:14.647 --> 10:17.515
♪♪

10:18.451 --> 10:22.286
<i>Clarence: Someone who inspires</i>
<i>me is my mom's boyfriend, Chad.</i>

10:22.321 --> 10:24.589
<i>Chad is really funny and fun.</i>

10:24.624 --> 10:26.491
<i>He isn't really good</i>
<i>at anything,</i>

10:26.526 --> 10:28.526
<i>and he sits around a lot.</i>

10:28.561 --> 10:30.995
<i>I think maybe it's hard</i>
<i>being a grown-up.</i>

10:31.030 --> 10:33.631
<i>There's no more school</i>
<i>or grades to get.</i>

10:33.666 --> 10:35.199
<i>Nobody tells you what to do,</i>

10:35.234 --> 10:37.935
<i>but that also means</i>
<i>maybe you don't do anything.</i>

10:37.970 --> 10:40.338
<i>And maybe it's okay</i>
<i>not to do anything,</i>

10:40.373 --> 10:43.841
<i>but if you want to do</i>
<i>something, it can be hard.</i>

10:43.876 --> 10:48.980
<i>I'm like Chad's coach,</i>
<i>but he's also my Chad Coach.</i>

10:49.015 --> 10:50.381
<i>I just want to be there</i>
<i>for Chad...</i>

10:50.416 --> 10:52.350
[ Cheering, dogs barking ]

10:52.385 --> 10:54.552
<i>...because he's there for me.</i>

10:55.555 --> 10:57.455
Ms. Baker: So, Clarence,
uh, do you have your essay

10:57.490 --> 10:59.190
on someone who inspires you?

10:59.225 --> 11:01.859
I fo-- I didn't do it.
Sorry.

11:01.894 --> 11:02.527
[ Rip! ]

11:02.562 --> 11:03.495
[ Ting! Ting! ]

11:05.531 --> 11:07.298
♪ Early to bed ♪

11:08.868 --> 11:10.935
♪ Early to rise ♪

11:12.505 --> 11:14.339
♪ Picking my nose ♪
